text.section:
A parent or legal guardian who borrows a hearing aid for an eligible child shall:
Be the custodian of the hearing aid;
Return the hearing aid immediately to the Loan Bank on the expiration of the loan period or receipt of a suitable permanent hearing aid, whichever occurs first;
Be responsible for the proper care and use of the hearing aid;
Be responsible for any damage to or loss of the hearing aid; and
Sign a written agreement provided by the State Superintendent that states the term and conditions of the loan.
